<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: anonymous</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-12 00:16:46</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>  hey all, this is my first post here so i will try to make it good.  fyi this info is more a warning than anything else, I have camped the bear for hours and never seen it.<BR>
   the bear spawns in a cave which is accessed by swimming in the western of the 2 tributaries on the north wall, under the ice, in everfrost. it is possible to reach the cave without end breath if you drop thru the closest hole and swim straight there. if you dont know how to go straight to it, i suggest a water breathing effect or spell.<BR>
   i am a level 45 cleric so here is my perspective inside the cave. there is a green con gobbie at the cavern entrance once you surface under the north wall. pass him up the hall a bit and there is a safe place to med. a bit further up the hall is a chamber with 4 exits.  do not enter this room. back up a bit so you can still see into it a bit.<BR>
   there is a wandering mob in the area that passes thru this room, named Lich of Miragul. he is an lvl 45 necro spell casting mob, with a preference to cast fear.  he also drags along a pet that conned blue to me and hits in the 60's. stay in your entrance passage to avoid this mob and watch the room to back off as he wanders thru it.  he never wanders south.<BR>
   as i understand the glacial bear has no ph and is set on a random timer. i also understand that it will wander thru the afore mentioned room.  <BR>
   more on the lich... 1 of his drops is a nice caster robe which is part of the fiery avenger quest.  he is a potent mob to be confronted by 1 group of very high levels or 2 groups 50ish.  nuff said. :)</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: anonymous</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-16 13:29:16</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white> addendum to the last post...<BR>
   I finally killed the glacier bear, and i said something very wrong in my last post. The bear does indeed have placeholders.  They are 2 wandering ice bone skellies that can be seen from my afore-mentioned vantage point.  Now here is the rub and why i thought there were no ph's before....<BR>
    This spawn is farmed by the know-hows.  You may never see the bear or a ph because people professionally hunt this bear, at least on the Brell server.<BR>
   What they do... plant a naked high-middle level ranger deep in the caves in one of two safe spots and camp him.  Log back on with this ranger to track for the bear or kill the ice bone phs.  The spawn time for them is about 8 hours, so if you kill the bear or the ph, you know almost exactly when to log back on.  Because of this, if you are sitting near the entrance of the cave, you may NEVER see a bear or ph, and have no clue what is happening deeper inside.<BR>
   Why do they do this...it's the nature of the beast. The bear pelt from Glacier Bear is part of Shaman Totemic Helm quest which sells for over 2k on my server right now.  The item droppers for the quest are EASY kills if you can wait out the spawn time, or coordinate your waiting periods.<BR>
   Unfortunately, because of this, many clerics will never own this shield because not only are the ingredients for the quest no-drop, but so is the shield itself.<BR>
   Good luck.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
