<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Keudiven</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-16 21:48:29</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white> Don't even waste your time. This quest is almost impossible. got the icon from mino caves very easily. the ingot however dropped from glacial bear, good luck. he is 7 to 8 hour spawn with many many place holders. Also he is for shaman totemic helm. he drops pelt 2 out of 3 drops and icon only 1 in 3. I got his spawn times down when I finally first found him (dropped pelt) . I have gotten him around the clock for 3 days now with 6 consecutive place holders so far. This will take weeks at this point waking up late at night everynight just to catch him. I WILL GET THAT INGOT.  wish me luck.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: kEUDIVEN</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-17 16:26:03</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white> By the rage of Lord Innoruuk, the shield is mine. To get the ingot from the glacial bear took absolute fanatical devotion. Hunted him around the clock for 3 days. First time i saw him he dropped the pelt, followed by 7 consecutive place holders. Finally the beast showed himself to me once again on the 9th spawn and he dropped both the ingot and the pelt. I discovered that when he does drop the ingot he also drops the pelt making this Bear far less frusterating for Shamans than for clerics. Also would like to add that his spawn rate is not absolute. Out of those 9 spawns he popped only once at exactly 8 hours, 5 times at 7.5 hours, 2 times at 7 hours and the last time he popped at 6.5 hours. One last thing to add. Both times he popped and almost every place holder spawned in the tunnel just east of Sulon McMoor and walked east. Good hunting!!!</font></td></tr></table>
